body:
```rust
use std::pin::Pin;

use futures::{Stream, StreamExt};

fn foo(stream: Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item=u32>>>) -> Option<Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item=u32>>>> {
    let res = Some(Box::pin(stream.map(|x| x)));
    res
}

fn main() {}
```
This code doesn't compile with following error:
```
error[E0308]: mismatched types
 --> src/main.rs:7:5
  |
5 | fn foo(stream: Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item=u32>>>) -> Option<Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item=u32>>>> {
  |                                                   -------------------------------------- expected `Option<Pin<Box<(dyn futures::Stream<Item = u32> + 'static)>>>` because of return type
6 |     let res = Some(Box::pin(stream.map(move |x| x)));
  |                                        ---------- the found closure
7 |     res
  |     ^^^ expected trait object `dyn futures::Stream`, found struct `futures::stream::Map`
  |
  = note: expected enum `Option<Pin<Box<(dyn futures::Stream<Item = u32> + 'static)>>>`
             found enum `Option<Pin<Box<futures::stream::Map<Pin<Box<dyn futures::Stream<Item = u32>>>, [closure@src/main.rs:6:40: 6:50]>>>>`

```
I found three ways to get around this error:
1. Change `dyn` to `impl`
```rust
fn foo(stream: Pin<Box<impl Stream<Item=u32>>>) -> Option<Pin<Box<impl Stream<Item=u32>>>> {
    let res = Some(Box::pin(stream.map(|x| x)));
    res
}
```
2. Remove `res` variable
```rust
fn foo(stream: Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item=u32>>>) -> Option<Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item=u32>>>> {
    Some(Box::pin(stream.map(|x| x)))
}
```
3. And, most confusing one: remove `Option` from function signature
```rust
fn foo(stream: Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item=u32>>>) -> Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item=u32>>> {
    let res = Box::pin(stream.map(|x| x));
    res
}
```


### Meta
This error appears in all latest channels (tested in rust playground)
